Limpopo Premier Stan Mathabatha has fired his provincial government spokesperson Phuti Seloba, for bringing his name and that of his administration into disrepute, but the defiant Seloba has promised not to go down without a fight. Mathabatha‘s office said Seloba was served with sanctions from the chairperson of the disciplinary hearing which recommended that he should be fired. The office confirmed on Sunday that Seloba has been fired. “Yes we can confirm that the Premier has fired Seloba. The premier was only acting on the recommendations of the chairperson of the disciplinary hearing, which recommended that Mr Seloba must be...